wikipedia_page.main: Edward 'Eddie' Frank Strong (born 1936), is a male former athlete who competed for England.

response: In 2004, Sanford attended the University of Mississippi, where his cousins Toward Sanford, Eddie Strong and Kevin Thomas played, but though he was signed to the team he was redshirted until 2005. That year, after briefly trying several positions, Sanford topped the depth chart as a strong safety, starting 10 out of 11 games in that position.
Another cousin, Eddie Strong, went undrafted in the 2003 NFL Draft but signed as a free agent rookie with the New York Giants in May 2003. He was released by New York 3 months later in August.
